          <p class="bio">Linfei (any/all) is a Psychology M.A. student in his last year at NSSR. His primary research interest is in investigating fluidity in human development, particularly the formation of multilingual, multicultural, and queer identities. He fully blames Language & Thought (which everyone should take in the spring) for getting him hooked on psycholinguistics. He currently manages the lab's Language Portraits project and is writing an M.A. thesis on sexual orientation fluidity in transitioning TGNC individuals. Outside the lab, Linfei can be found birdbanding during the spring and fall migrations.</p>
